        rdfs:comment     "A hallmark phenotype seen in Abcc6-/- mice is the spontaneous gradual calcification of the connective tissue surrounding the vibrissae " , "Abcc6-/- mice recapitulate human PXE, with calcifying lesions found in skin, eyes, and blood vessels " , "cryo-injury applied to the heart results in calcified lesions within 3 – 6 days, a phenomenon fully dependent on the absence of Abcc6." , "Enpp1-/- mice have extensive calcifications in blood vessels and joints\nshortly after birth, develop extensive calcification of the\ndermal sheet surrounding the vibrissae." ;
